    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="863"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/398.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Representative</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Liberian loan negotiations have been concluded. German creditors will accept 90
                    for their scheduled debts, after payment of which the same terms for
                    subsequently created debts. The bankers should provide for prompt disbursement
                    if they are satisfied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
